-----------------------------------------------------------
KEY TAKEAWAYS
-----------------------------------------------------------

When source code has a decoding function but never calls it, that is your hint. You need to trigger that function yourself either by editing the file or writing your own script.

ROT47 is an extension of ROT13. Same concept, bigger character set. Both are self-reversing.

Reading code carefully before running anything saves a lot of time. The solution was already written inside the file. You just had to understand it and use it correctly.

Bugs in provided code are sometimes intentional in CTF challenges. Part of the challenge is identifying what is wrong and fixing it.
